- other limit properties
</details>
<details class="algorithm" open><summary>Evaluate $\displaystyle\lim_{x\to0}f(x)$</summary>
- use mathmatical maturity to suspect that DNE
  - e.g. approach along $x=ky$
  - e.g. approach along $x=x\quad y=0\quad z=0$
  - to show limit not unique
- use $\delta$-$\varepsilon$ to show limit exists
  - $p(x)/q(x)$ where $p$ has higher power $\implies$ exists
  - use $x^2\le x^2+y^2\quad |x|\le\sqrt{x^2+y^2}$
  - $f(x,y)$ only has $x^2+y^2\implies$ use $r=\sqrt{x^2+y^2}$ and $r\to0^+$
  - use sandwich theorem
</details>
<details class="example"><summary>use **$x^2\le x^2+y^2+z^2$** for $\displaystyle\lim_{v\to0}\frac{x^2y^2z^2}{x^2+y^2+z^2}=0$</summary>
wts $\forall\varepsilon>0\enspace\exist\delta>0$ st
$$0<||(x,y,z)||=\sqrt{x^2+y^2+z^2}<\delta\implies\left|\frac{x^2y^2z^2}{x^2+y^2+z^2}\right|<\varepsilon$$

aside
$$\begin{align*}
  \because x^2,y^2,z^2&\le x^2+y^2+z^2\\
  \therefore\left|\frac{x^2y^2z^2}{x^2+y^2+z^2}\right|&=\frac{x^2y^2z^2}{x^2+y^2+z^2}\le\frac{(x^2+y^2+z^2)^3}{x^2+y^2+z^2}\\
  &=(x^2+y^2+z^2)^2<\delta^4=\varepsilon\\
\end{align*}$$

proof: given $\varepsilon>0$ let $\delta=\sqrt[4]\varepsilon>0$
$$\begin{align*}
  \therefore0<||(x,y,z)||<\delta\implies\left|\frac{x^2y^2z^2}{x^2+y^2+z^2}\right|&\le(x^2+y^2+z^2)^2\\ &<\delta^2=\varepsilon\quad\blacksquare
\end{align*}$$
</details>
<details class="example"><summary>use **upper bound** for $\displaystyle\lim_{(x,y)\to(a,b)}xy=ab$</summary>
wts $\forall\varepsilon>0\enspace\exist\delta>0$ st 
$$0<\sqrt{(x-a)^2+(y-b)^2}<\delta\implies|xy-ab|<\varepsilon$$

aside: assume $\delta\le1$
$$\begin{align*}
  \because |y-b|&\le\sqrt{(x-a)^2+(y-b)^2}<\delta\\
  \therefore|y|-|b|&\le|y-b|<\delta\le1\\
  \therefore|y|&\le|b|+1\\
  \\
  \therefore|xy-ab|&=|xy-ay+ay-ab|=|x-a||y|+|a||y-b|\\
  &\le|x-a|(|b|+1)+|y-b||a|\\
  &\le\sqrt{(x-a)^2+(y-b)^2}(|a|+|b|+1)\\
  &\le(|a|+|b|+1)\delta=\varepsilon
\end{align*}$$

proof: given $\varepsilon>0$ let $\delta=\textrm{min}(1,\varepsilon/(1+|a|+|b|))>0$

</details>
<details class="example"><summary>use **$x=ky$** for $\displaystyle\lim_{v\to0}\frac{5y^4\cos^2x}{x^4+y^4}$ DNE</summary>
as $(x,y)\to(0,0)$ along $y=kx$

$$\lim_{v\to0}f(x,y)=\lim_{v\to0}\frac{5k^4x^4\cos^2x}{x^4k^4x^4}=\lim_{v\to0}\frac{5k^4\cos^2x}{1+k^4}=\frac{5k^4}{1+k^4}$$

$\therefore$ limit depends on $k$<br>
$\therefore$ limit is not unique<br>
$\therefore$ limit DNE
</details>
<details class="example"><summary>use **sandwich** for $\displaystyle\lim_{(x,y)\to(1^+,0)}\frac{(x-1)^2\ln x}{(x-1)^2+y^2}=0$</summary>
$$\begin{align*}
  \because 0&\le(x-1)^2\le(x-1)^2+y^2\\
  \therefore0&\le\frac{(x-1)^2}{(x-1)^2+y^2}\le1\\
  \because0&\le\ln x\enspace\forall x>1\\
  \therefore0&\le\frac{(x-1)\ln x}{(x-1)^2+y^2}\le\ln x\\
  \therefore0&\le\lim_{(x,y)\to(1^+,0)}\frac{(x-1)^2\ln x}{(x-1)^2+y^2}\le\lim_{x\to1^+}\ln x=0\\
\end{align*}$$
</details>
<details class="example"><summary>use **substitution** for $\displaystyle\lim_{v\to0}(x^2+y^2)\ln(x^2+y^2)$</summary>
let $r^2=x^2+y^2$<br>
let $r^2\to t\quad t>0$
$$\begin{align*}
  \lim_{v\to0}(x^2+y^2)\ln(x^2+y^2)&=\lim_{r\to0}r^2\ln(r^2)\\
  &=\lim_{t\to0^+}\frac{\ln t}{1/t}=\lim_{t\to0^+}-t=0\\
\end{align*}$$
</details>

